              <div class="example" id="header-based-routing">
                  <div class="col-xs-11 col-sm-11 col-md-11">
                      <h2><a href="./">Ballerina by Example</a>: Header Based Routing</h2>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-1 col-sm-1 col-md-1">
                      <a href="./" class="cBackButton"><img src="http://b.content.wso2.com/sites/all/ballerina/backbutton.svg"/></a>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12">

                      

                      <table>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>The Header-Based Router service reads a particular Header of a message and routes it to a specific recipient based on the Header value.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nx">ballerina</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">net</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nx">ballerina</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">lang</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">messages</span><span class="p">;</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Service is invoke using BasePath value (/hbr).</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="nd">@http:config {</span><span class="nx">basePath</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s">&quot;/hbr&quot;</span><span class="p">}</span>
<span class="kd">service</span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">&gt;</span> <span class="nx">headerBasedRouting</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>http:GET{} annotation declares the HTTP method.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>    <span class="nd">@http:GET {</span><span class="p">}</span>
    <span class="nd">@http:Path {</span><span class="nx">value</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s">&quot;/route&quot;</span><span class="p">}</span>
    <span class="kd">resource</span> <span class="nx">hbrResource</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">message</span> <span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Create two service endpoints using HTTP client-connector with different hosts.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>        <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span> <span class="nx">locationEP</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="nx">create</span> <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span><span class="p">(</span>
                                          <span class="s">&quot;http://www.mocky.io&quot;</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span> <span class="nx">weatherEP</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="nx">create</span> <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span><span class="p">(</span>
                                         <span class="s">&quot;http://samples.openweathermap.org&quot;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Native function getHeader() returns header value of a specified header name.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>        <span class="kt">string</span> <span class="nx">nameString</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="nx">messages</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">getHeader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&quot;type&quot;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  
                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>        <span class="kt">message</span> <span class="nx">response</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="p">{};</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">nameString</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;location&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>&ldquo;post&rdquo; represent the POST action of HTTP connector. Route payload to relevant service.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>            <span class="nx">response</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">post</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">locationEP</span><span class="p">,</span>
                                       <span class="s">&quot;/v2/594e12271100001f13d6d3a6&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">);</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>If requested resources needed some partial modifications, PATCH method will add them.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>            <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">patch</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">locationEP</span><span class="p">,</span>
                                       <span class="s">&quot;/v2/594e12271100001f13d6d3a6&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">);</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  
                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>        <span class="p">}</span> <span class="k">else</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>&ldquo;execute&rdquo; action can be used to invoke http call with any httpVerb by adding verb as parameter.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>            <span class="kt">message</span> <span class="nx">newMessage</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="p">{};</span>
            <span class="nx">response</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">execute</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">weatherEP</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&quot;GET&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span>
                                       <span class="s">&quot;/data/2.5/weather?lat=35&amp;lon=139&amp;appid=b1b1&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span>
                                       <span class="nx">newMessage</span><span class="p">);</span>
        <span class="p">}</span>
        <span class="nx">reply</span> <span class="nx">response</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                      </table>


                      

